properties.areaDesc: Lake Superior from Upper Entrance to Portage Canal to Manitou Island MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian Border; Upper Entrance of Portage Canal to Eagle River MI; Eagle River to Manitou Island MI
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 1 at 9:44AM EST until February 2 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and waves
7 to 10 feet expected.

* WHERE...Lake Superior from Upper Entrance to Portage Canal to
Manitou Island MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian Border,
Upper Entrance of Portage Canal to Eagle River MI and Eagle
River to Manitou Island MI.

* WHEN...From 11 AM to 7 PM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 11 AM TO 7 PM EST SUNDAY
